    <div xml:id="PN301">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>palcāṉ ṟīrē palcāṉ ṟīrē</l>
<l>kumari makaḷir kūntal puraiya</l>
<l>vamari ṉiṭṭa varumuḷ vēlik</l>
<l>kalleṉ pācaṟaip palcāṉ ṟīrē</l>
<l>muracumuḻaṅku tāṉainu maracu mōmpumi</l>
<l>ṉoḷiṟēntu maruppiṉuṅ kaḷiṟum pōṟṟumi</l>
<l>ṉeṉaināṭ ṭaṅkunum pōrē yaṉainā</l>
<l>ḷeṟiyā reṟital yāvaṇa teṟintō</l>
<l>retirceṉ ṟeṟitaluñ cellā ṉataṉā</l>
<l>laṟintōr yāravaṉ kaṇṇiya poruḷē</l>
<l>palameṉ ṟikaḻta lōmpumi ṉutukkā</l>
<l>ṇilaṉaḷap paṉṉa nillāk kuṟuneṟi</l>
<l>vaṇparip puravip paṇpupā rāṭṭi</l>
<l>yelliṭaip paṭartan tōṉē kalleṉa</l>
<l>vēntūr yāṉaik kalla</l>
<l>tēntuvaṉ pōlāṉṟa ṉilaṅkilai vēlē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>You who deserve much [praise]! You who deserve much [praise]!(1)</l>
<l>In the noisy camp with a fence of difficult thorns</l>
<l>put because of the battle, resembling the tresses</l>
<l>of virgin girls, you who deserve much [praise] (2-4)!</l>
<l>Protect your king with a thundering drum [and] an army (5)</l>
<l>and praise your elephant bulls with bright eminent tusks. (6)</l>
<l>As many days as your war with last, for so many days, (7)</l>
<l>where will be attacking those who don’t attack? He won’t go</l>
<l>attacking even against those who attacked. Therefore, (8f.)</l>
<l>who are those who know the object he has in mind? (10)</l>
<l>Beware of deriding [him], thinking “we are many!” Look there! (11)</l>
<l>Praising the qualities of the horse with generous motion (13)</l>
<l>on the short path that does not stand, as if measuring the ground, (12)</l>
<l>there is one who sets out at night, noisily. (14)</l>
<l>It seems he will not raise his spear with a shining leaf[-tip] (16)</l>
<l>except for the elephant mounted by the king. (15)</l>
</lg>
